# PR Numbering

When starting work for a new PR, assign the next ascending PR number `x` by checking the most recent prior PR title or commit subject that uses `[PR-y]`.

- If the latest seen number is `[PR-4]`, the next new PR number is `5`
- Reuse that same `x` for the whole branch until the PR is finished
- Do not invent a fresh number for later commits on the same PR branch

## Formats

- Git branch name: use a git-safe form like `pr-5-short-summary`
- Commit subject: use `[PR-5] short summary`
- PR title: use `[PR-5] short summary`

## Quick Rule

- New PR branch: increment to the next number once
- Same branch, later commits: keep the same number
- Only increment again when starting a different new PR branch
